Program: The Forum
Title: Shame
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02nk89n
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 14 Apr 2015
Can shame be a force for good? Or is it always in danger of being a tool of repression? Bridget Kendall explores shame with evolutionary biologist Dan Fessler, philosopher A.C Grayling and environmental social scientist Jennifer Jacquet. Photo: A person feeling shame (BBC/ Shan Pillay)